config NXP_EVTG
	bool "NXP EVTG (Event Generator) driver"
	default y
	depends on DT_HAS_NXP_EVTG_ENABLED
	select CLOCK_CONTROL
	help
	  Enable the NXP EVTG (Event Generator) driver. The EVTG combines up to
	  four inputs through two AND/OR/INVERT blocks and an optional flip-flop
	  to produce an event-generator output on select NXP microcontrollers.
	  Each used EVTG instance is described by a devicetree child node and is
	  programmed statically at init time; the driver wraps the fsl_evtg HAL
	  and exposes no runtime API.
